<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFF42FA9CFD80FAA0" box="[248,537,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Zanoni &amp; Pimentel 40315</emphasis>
(JBSD, MO, NY).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3606530B31B8A0DFF0EFABCFBA9FEED" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31B8A0DFF0EFABCFD68F910" blockId="8.[151,753,1152,1981]" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
Although Lamarck’s protologue indicates that the plant collected by Joseph Martin came from Martinique, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFF44FAF1FE6CFA04" box="[254,501,1386,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crotonoides">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFF44FAF1FE6CFA04" box="[254,501,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Solanum crotonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been collected there. A similar situation exists for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFDC1FA17FF25FA47" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrifolium">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFDC1FA17FF25FA47" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. pyrifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Dulcamaroid clade), also collected by Martin from “Martinique”. I suspect that Martin did in fact also visit Hispaniola (the locality for his type collection of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFEB3F989FE64F9AC" box="[265,509,1554,1580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Aquartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphylla">Aquartia microphylla</taxonomicName>
is “S. Domingo”, see below) or that Martin used Martinique as a broad locality covering most of the Caribbean region, and that both these plants are true Hispaniolan endemics.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31B8A0DFF0EF903FE76F8FA" blockId="8.[151,753,1152,1981]" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
In describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFEEDF903FD69F932" authority=", Schulz and Schmidt" authorityName="Schulz and Schmidt" box="[343,752,1688,1714]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formonense">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFEEDF903FE6FF932" box="[343,502,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. formonense</emphasis>
, Schulz and Schmidt
</taxonomicName>
did not designate which of the two varieties was typical. Sheets of both syntypes are held at S; 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFD27F940FF60F896" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Ekman H.10365</emphasis>
(S04-2911, 
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB31B8A0DFE3BF967FE4BF896" box="[385,466,1788,1814]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[181,215,1854,1875]" captionTargetBox="[234,1383,205,1826]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. a, lectotype of Solanum chamaeacanthum Griseb., Wright s.n. (GOET0001971); b, lectotype of S. hoplophorum O.E. Schulz, Fuertes 1023 (S04-2916) (= S.crotonoides Lam.).Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History; c, lectotype of S. formonense O.E. Schulz and of S. formonense var. parvifolium O.E. Schulz,Ekman H.10265 (S04-2911) (= S. crotonoides Lam.). Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History; d, lectotype of S. dendroicum O.E.Schulz &amp; Ekman, Ekman H.15102 (S04-2902). Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326312/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
) is in excellent condition and is here used to lectotypify both the species and the variety. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFF57F8A4FE01F8D9" box="[237,408,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Ekman H.7461</emphasis>
is the lectotype for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFDC9F8A4FF79F8FA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="formonense" variety="grandifolium">
var. 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFD1BF8A4FF79F8FA" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">grandifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is not figured here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31B8A0DFF0EF819FBA9FEED" blockId="8.[151,753,1152,1981]" lastBlockId="8.[805,1406,207,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
The lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFECFF819FDBFF81C" authorityName="O. E. Schulz, Fuertes" authorityYear="1023" box="[373,550,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoplophorum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFECFF819FDBFF81C" box="[373,550,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. hoplophorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB31B8A0DFD8FF819FD1CF81C" box="[565,645,1922,1948]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[181,215,1854,1875]" captionTargetBox="[234,1383,205,1826]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. a, lectotype of Solanum chamaeacanthum Griseb., Wright s.n. (GOET0001971); b, lectotype of S. hoplophorum O.E. Schulz, Fuertes 1023 (S04-2916) (= S.crotonoides Lam.).Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History; c, lectotype of S. formonense O.E. Schulz and of S. formonense var. parvifolium O.E. Schulz,Ekman H.10265 (S04-2911) (= S. crotonoides Lam.). Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History; d, lectotype of S. dendroicum O.E.Schulz &amp; Ekman, Ekman H.15102 (S04-2902). Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326312/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
) is a very robust, prickly male plant 
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFE6CF838FD1CF83D" box="[470,645,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">(Fuertes 1023),</emphasis>
showing that combination of characters that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B4AB31B8A0DFB09FF54FAD3FF69" author="Dunal, M. - F." box="[1203,1354,207,233]" editor="J. L. M. Poiret" journalOrPublisher="Chez H. Agasse" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" pagination="738 - 780" part="3" refId="ref13617" refString="Dunal, M. - F. 1814. Morelle, Solanum. In: J. L. M. Poiret (ed.), Encyclopedie methodique, Botanique, Suppl. 3: 738 - 780. Paris: Chez H. Agasse." title="Morelle, Solanum" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Encyclopedie methodique, Botanique" year="1814">Dunal (1814)</bibRefCitation>
noted in describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFC54FF6BFB15FE8A" box="[1006,1164,240,266]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFC54FF6BFB15FE8A" box="[1006,1164,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. reticulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the “hermaphrodite” of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFC3DFE8AFBBBFEAB" box="[903,1058,273,299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crotonoides">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFC3DFE8AFBBBFEAB" box="[903,1058,273,299]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. crotonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which is a dioecious species, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B4AB31B8A0DFCE8FEA9FBAAFECC" author="Knapp, S. &amp; Persson, V. &amp; Blackmore, S." box="[850,1075,306,332]" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" pagination="113 - 139" part="210" refId="ref14218" refString="Knapp, S., Persson, V. &amp; Blackmore, S. 1998. Pollen morphology and functional dioecy in Solanum (Solanaceae). Plant Systematics and Evolution 210: 113 - 139." title="Pollen morphology and functional dioecy in Solanum (Solanaceae)" type="journal article" year="1998">Knapp &amp; al., 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Both varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D38B31B8A0DFAAFFEA9FCFDFEED" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formonense">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B31B8A0DFAAFFEA9FCFDFEED" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="73">S. formonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are female plants.
</paragraph>
